name: Self Portrait As Man Ray
description:
Man Ray (1890 – 1976) was an American artist who spent most of his career in Paris. He was also an important contributor to the Dada movement and Surrealism. Apart from being a painter he is also known as a pioneer in art and fashion photography. Some of his famous works use photograms and refer to them as Rayographs.

this image in 2144 px X 2667 px
